This directory contains ASCII data files for the Oke (AJ,
99, 1621, 1990) optical spectrophotometric standard stars. 

The files with prefix 'm' list wavelength (A), AB magnitude
and the bandpass used in measurement.

The files with prefix 'f' list wavelength (A), flux 
(ergs/cm/cm/s/A * 10**16), flux (milli-Jy) and the bandpass 
used in measurement.

The files can be converted to MIDAS tables (.TBL). DOITOKE.PRG 
is the MIDAS procedure to convert all the files and FORMAT.FMT 
is the format file for the tables.

There is an explanatory text and finding charts available for 
these standard stars. These are available on the World Wide Web
(http://www.eso.org/spect-phot-standards/optuvstandards.html) 
or contact J. R. Walsh (jwalsh@eso.org) for details. 

July 1995

-----------

Updated website (J. Moustakas, 2002 June 12)
http://www.eso.org/observing/standards/spectra/okestandards.html:

Oke (1990) Spectrophotometric Standards

Oke (AJ, 99, 1621, 1990) has provided absolute spectral energy distributions covering the
wavelength range 3200 to 9200A in AB magnitudes for 25 stars. The measurements were made
with the Double Beam Spectrogrpph of the Hale 5m telescope. The reduced magnitudes are
tabulated at 1A intervals from 3300 to 4700A and at 2A intervals from 4700 to 9200A.
Comparison of the fluxes with those determined elsewhere showed that Oke's absolute
magnitudes are systematically brighter by 0.04 mag. The magnitudes and fluxes plotted have
been corrected for this effect. Colina & Bohlin (AJ, 1931, 1994) tabulate the differences
between the original Oke fluxes, in terms of synthesized B and V magnitudes, and Landolt
photometry for each star individually. The AB magnitudes were converted to flux
(ergs/cm/cm/s/A) using the formula 
ABMAG = -2.5 alog10(Fnu) - 48.59 
(Hamuy et al., PASP, 104, 533, 1992), where Fnu is in ergs/cm/cm/s/Hz.

